<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-19T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-19T04:00:00-05:00" n="1343" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1343">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8–1949: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="32" xml:id="d1343fn32">Text printed from corrected copy
                                received August 19, 11 p. m.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-19T17:00:00+08:00">August 19,
                                    1949—5 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 19—5:43 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3341. Attempted bombing customs lighthouse tenders August 18, 3 p.m.
                            (ConGentel 3311, August 18<note n="33" xml:id="d1343fn33">Not
                                printed.</note>), illustrates essentiality prompt assurances
                            responsible authorities Canton and Taipei safe conduct, noninterference
                            proposed call <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi> September 17 if withdrawal
                            Americans on that vessel to succeed. Safe conduct given by Chinese
                            Nationalist Government Canton probably insufficient protect evacuation
                            vessels from bold daylight aerial attacks based on Taiwan unless
                            Generalissimo notified and his personal assurance obtained.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department; repeated OffEmb Canton 1029.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>